modules.description: Provides functions to convert an abstract data type to an S-expression, retrieve a numeric value representing sequence length, and generate a string representation using tail-recursive traversal. Works with an opaque type encapsulating sequence data. Used to serialize test data for debugging and to extract metadata during validation checks.

Provides operations for building and manipulating rope data structures, including concatenation, conversion to strings, and efficient handling of large or complex string constructions. Works with tree-based representations of strings, where each node contains a substring or references to child nodes. Useful for scenarios like prettyprinting abstract syntax trees, where frequent concatenation and restructuring of strings occur without unnecessary copying.

Encapsulates a sequence as an opaque type, supporting conversion to S-expressions, retrieval of length as a numeric value, and generation of string representations via tail-recursive traversal. Enables serialization of test data and metadata extraction during validation. Operations include `to_sexp`, `length`, and `to_string`. Example uses include debugging with structured data and validating sequence properties through length checks.
